<font color="#FF0000">HELPING HAND &amp; WELCOME HOME</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  1 21:26:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
I had been to washington a couple of times after the wall had been deicated but for me a survivor,(Navy72-76) one who never had a chance to serve with those who went before me I felt a guilt that was so overwelming that I felt staying away would be the best way for me to show respect for those who went and did not return. Until I met Chet Botkins who literaly took me to the wall to show me that this is where I needed to be. Chet showed me how I could contribute to the healing of others by a simple handshake a sincere &quot;Welcome Home&quot;. From that May 1987 my healing proscess started and will continue till I die because I for one will not forget the ones who did not come back nor will I pass the living without a &quot;Welcome Home &quot; thank you Chet and Welcome Home bro!<br>
 
